Date: 0/0/1881
Source: Waitaruna
Author: BATHGATE
Vol / Page: 53
Edition:
Quote: That's the team of working bullocks we have just passed; we have names for them, as you'll know when you come to try your hand at punching them. <i>Ibid.</i> 67 He can punch the bullocks almost as well as an old hand already, even to the swearing at them.
Notes:

Date: 0/0/1888
Source: Antipodean Notes
Author: D'AVIGDOR
Vol / Page: 170
Edition:
Quote: A <i>bullock puncher </i>is a man engaged to drive bullocks to market or port. The expression is painfully true, as these men, who receive but very poor wages, are recruited from the worst class, ill-treat the poor animals by <i>punching</i> their sides with pointed stick.
